TWO tsotsis were killed while another two were arrested after a cash-in-transit robbery in Delmas, Mpumalanga, on Monday, 28 February. Police spokesman Brigadier Selvy Mohlala said a cash delivery van with two security guards was attacked by a group of heavily armed suspects. “The suspects then tried to rob the guards, but their efforts were quashed. Police were alerted and swiftly went to the scene. “A shoot-out with the police ensued and two suspects were fatally shot while two others reportedly hijacked a Toyota Quantum minibus. “The police gave chase and arrested the two suspects, aged 24 and 34. The rest of the suspects fled the scene,” said Mohlala.He said cops recovered a rifle an d magazines, jamming devices and police radios. “Police also confiscated a white Porsche Cayenne and a silver BMW SUV, which were allegedly used by the suspects in the robbery. “Police are still on the lookout for the remaining suspects. “Police are still on the scene and more evidence may be uncovered,” he said. “The two suspects are expected to appear in the Delmas District Court soon on charges of armed robbery, possession of a firearm and ammunition and possession of explosives. More charges could be laid against the suspects.” Mpumalanga Police Commissioner Lieutenant-General Semakaleng Manamela praised the police for their swift response. “People should take note that Mpumalanga is not a place where criminals do as they like,” Manamela said. “The formidable team of our members is ever-ready to meet fire with fire.”